TY  - JOUR
T1  - Reconceptualizing Workplace Commitment to Redress a Stretched Construct: Revisiting Assumptions and Removing Confounds
AU  - Klein, Howard J.
AU  - Molloy, Janice C.
AU  - Brinsfield, Chad T.
Y1  - 2012/01/01
PY  - 2012
DA  - 2012/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2010.0018
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2010.0018
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 130
EP  - 151
VL  - 37
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - To better understand the workplace commitments experienced by organizational members, we reconceptualize commitment to highlight its distinctiveness and improve its applicability across all workplace targets. We present a continuum of psychological bonds and reconceptualize commitment as a particular type of bond reflecting volitional dedication and responsibility for a target. We then present a process model applicable to any workplace target to bring clarity, consistency, and synergy to the research and management of workplace commitments.
AB  - To better understand the workplace commitments experienced by organizational members, we reconceptualize commitment to highlight its distinctiveness and improve its applicability across all workplace targets. We present a continuum of psychological bonds and reconceptualize commitment as a particular type of bond reflecting volitional dedication and responsibility for a target. We then present a process model applicable to any workplace target to bring clarity, consistency, and synergy to the research and management of workplace commitments.
