TY  - JOUR
T1  - Reflections on the 2010 AMR Decade Award: Whither the Promise? Moving Forward with Entrepreneurship As a Science of the Artificial
AU  - Venkataraman, Sankaran
AU  - Sarasvathy, Saras D.
AU  - Dew, Nicholas
AU  - Forster, William R.
Y1  - 2012/01/01
PY  - 2012
DA  - 2012/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2011.0079
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2011.0079
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 21
EP  - 33
VL  - 37
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this article we speak of roads taken and paths yet to be traversed. Over the past decade, entrepreneurship researchers have accumulated considerable work related to opportunities. Here we outline new possibilities opened up by that work and seek to recast entrepreneurship as a science of the artificial in three ways: understanding opportunities as made as well as found, moving beyond new combinations to transformations, and developing a new nexus around actions and interactions.
AB  - In this article we speak of roads taken and paths yet to be traversed. Over the past decade, entrepreneurship researchers have accumulated considerable work related to opportunities. Here we outline new possibilities opened up by that work and seek to recast entrepreneurship as a science of the artificial in three ways: understanding opportunities as made as well as found, moving beyond new combinations to transformations, and developing a new nexus around actions and interactions.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2011.0079
